whitebait
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the fry of <i>Galaxias</i> and <i>Retropinna</i> spp. (esp. <i>R. richardsonii</i>), bait, inanga, inaka (cf (s)cent, silvery smelt; gutty bait) also called bait, inanga the young of a group of small fishes, in New Zealand especially galaxias, regarded as a table delicacy.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: incl fig (hasn't got the guts of a whitebait)
