Date: 0/0/1898
Source: Austral English
Author: MORRIS
Vol / Page: 510
Edition:
Quote: <i>Whitebait, n</i>. a fish; not, as in England, the fry of the herring and sprat, but in Victoria, <i>Engraulis antarcticus</i>, Cast ln.; and in New Zealand, the young fry of <i>Galaxias attenuatus,</i> Jenyns (<i>Inanga</i>, q.v.). The young of the <i>New Zealand Smelt</i> (q.v.), <i>Retropinna richardsonii</i>, Gill, are also called <i>Whitebait</i>, both in New Zealand and in Tasmania.
