Date: 0/5/1922
Source: NZ Journal of Science & Technology
Author:
Vol / Page: V/94
Edition:
Quote: RETROPINNA RETROPINNA. <i>Smelt</i>. The larval smelt, which has a strong cucumber-smell, is rarely sold as `whitebait.' Canning-factories at Hokitika do not purchase any fish under the term `whitebait' other than the larval <i>Galaxias attenuatus</i>. Odd smelts may occasionally be detected among whitebait exposed for sale in Wellington... GALAXIAS ATTENUATUS. <i>Minnow</i>. All whitebait examined from Auckland were found to be referable to this species. Whitebait were exposed for sale in Auckland during August, September, and October.
Notes: Phillipps and Hodgkinson Further Notes on Edible Fishes

